    • jsonBigDecimal

      public static <P extends PreciseValue<? super P>> com.google.gson.JsonPrimitive jsonBigDecimal​(P preciseValue)
      In theory, we want to write this out with perfect precision. return new JsonPrimitive(preciseValue.asBigDecimal()); In practice, we don't care about that much detail, so it doesn't matter. However, more importantly, many of the PreciseValues used are generated with the output of optimizer, so they may be precise, but not accurate. If we don't round to 8 digits, then the JSON may record something like 100.000000000001, which we don't really want, because the JSON comparisons we use aren't 'epsilon comparisons', so they would cause tests to fail.
